VC (Volume Control Ventilation)

During Volume Control ventilation, tidal volume can be set for mandatory breaths. If a volume setting is changed while the ventilator is operating, the change takes place in increments over a series of breaths.

When tidal volume is adjusted, inspiratory time remains constant and mandatory flow changes.

If an attempted tidal volume setting results in a flow rate in excess of 100 L/min or less than 6 L/min, flow adjustment ceases, the user is alerted by an audible beep, and a message appears in the Message Display Window. To allow further volume adjustment, change the inspiratory time to set the Flow to meet the need of the patient.



